Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-only tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]
// Or simpler, if on .NET 5+:
[TestMethod]
[System.Runtime.InteropServices.OSPlatform("windows")]
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
    // ... registry code
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");
    // ... GPU code
}
```

Then exclude in CI via: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

## 3. Flaky external API — retry pattern

```csharp
// Custom retry attribute (MSTest v3+)
[TestMethod]
[RetryAttribute(MaxRetryCount = 3)]
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    var result = CallWeatherApi();
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

For older MSTest without built-in retry, use a helper:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void WeatherApiTest()
{
    RetryHelper.Execute(maxAttempts: 3, () =>
    {
        var result = CallWeatherApi();
        Assert.IsNotNull(result);
    });
}
```

## 4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup] // Runs even if the test fails or throws
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void WriteTempFileTest()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        Assert.IsTrue(File.Exists(_tempFile));
    }
}
```

**Summary:**

| Scenario | Approach |
|----------|----------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` guard or condition attribute |
| Skip in CI | `[TestCategory]` + filter, or env-var guard |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry]` (MSTest v3+) or manual retry helper |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` (always runs post-test) |
